OL,3,CJersey politician guilty of offences
OL,4,Clinked to employing Rwandan nationals
OL,6,FIn September, Deputy Ozouf was
OL,7,Fsuspended for 28 days without pay
OL,8,Fafter breaching the States' Code of
OL,9,FConduct multiple times.
OL,11,FThis was in relation to him being
OL,12,Fcaught driving at 31mph in a 15mph
OL,13,Fzone without displaying valid car
OL,14,Finsurance in November 2024.
OL,16,FOn Monday 8 September, Deputy Ozouf
OL,17,Foffered "a full and unreserved
OL,18,Fapology" in the States Chamber to
OL,19,Fthose specific offences.
OL,21,FHe is due to be sentenced in February.
